# FitCoach Design System — AI Code Generation Guardrail

description: Enforces simplified 3-layer public API for all UI code generation
globs: ["src/**/*.tsx", "src/**/*.ts", "src/**/*.css"]

---

## NON-NEGOTIABLE RULE

The FitCoach design system has ONLY 3 public concepts.

1. **theme** — semantic tokens (bg-background, text-foreground, etc.)
2. **ui** — primitive components and contracts
3. **viz** — ONE function: `useDesignViz(domain, value)`

If you need a color → **default to THEME DOMAIN ONLY**
If you need a viz color → **use `useDesignViz()` ONLY**

---

## Mental Model (15 Seconds)

```
Need a UI color?    → use theme tokens
Need a layout?      → use ui primitives
Need a health viz?  → use useDesignViz()
```

That's it. No renderer, no registry, no scale, no mapper.
Those are internal. You never import them.

---

## Public API Reference

### Theme
```tsx
// Allowed
<div className="bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4">
  <h2 className="text-foreground font-bold">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground">Description</p>
</div>
```

**Allowed tokens:** `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-card`, `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `bg-accent`, `text-accent-foreground`, `bg-destructive`, `text-destructive-foreground`, `bg-success`, `text-success-foreground`, `bg-warning`, `text-warning-foreground`

**Forbidden:** `text-white`, `bg-black`, `bg-zinc-950`, `text-gray-400`, `#FFFFFF`, `rgba(255,255,255,0.3)`

### UI Primitives
```tsx
import { PRIMITIVE_COLOR_MAP, PrimitiveVariant } from "@/design-system/ui";
```

### Visualization (ONLY this)
```tsx
import { useDesignViz } from "@/design-system/viz";

const visual = useDesignViz("fatigue", 75);
// visual.tailwind.bg  → "bg-warning/40"
// visual.tailwind.text → "text-warning"
// visual.surface       → CSS color string

<div className={visual.tailwind.bg}>
  <span className={visual.tailwind.text}>High Fatigue</span>
</div>
```

**❌ FORBIDDEN (will fail lint + scanner):**
```tsx
import { renderVisualState } from "@/design-system/visualization/core/renderer"
import { mapFatigueToScale } from "@/design-system/visualization/domains/fatigue"
import { getDomain } from "@/design-system/visualization/registry"
import { fatiguePalette } from "@/design-system/visualization/fatigue"
```

---

## Before Generating Code

Ask yourself ONE question:

> Is this color describing a physiological/business state?

- **No** → Use theme tokens
- **Yes** → Use `useDesignViz()`

---

## Violation Examples (NEVER GENERATE)

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-zinc-950 text-white">

// ❌ WRONG: viz color in UI
<button className="bg-orange-500">Start Workout</button>

// ❌ WRONG: direct internal viz import
import { renderVisualState } from "@/design-system/visualization/core/renderer";

// ❌ WRONG: inline hex
<div style={{ background: '#0a0a0a' }}>

// ❌ WRONG: rgba without semantic var
<div style={{ color: 'rgba(255,255,255,0.4)' }}>
```

---

## File Location Rules (Phase 13)

| File Path | Allowed Imports |
|-----------|---------------|
| `src/design-system/theme/*` | Theme only |
| `src/design-system/ui/*` | Theme, Primitive |
| `src/design-system/viz/*` | Visualization internals (registry, renderer) |
| `src/components/**` | `@/design-system/theme`, `@/design-system/ui`, `@/design-system/viz` |
| `src/app/**` | `@/design-system/theme`, `@/design-system/ui`, `@/design-system/viz` |

**Critical:** Components in `src/components/` and `src/app/` may ONLY import from the 3 public APIs (`theme/`, `ui/`, `viz/`). Never from `visualization/`, `primitives/`, or `core/`.

---

## Consequence of Violation

If you generate code that violates these rules:
1. CI will fail (`pnpm lint`)
2. Boundary scanner will fail (`npx tsx scripts/enforce-design-boundaries.ts`)
3. Cognitive load scanner will fail (`npx tsx scripts/check-cognitive-load.ts`)
4. Theme will break for dark OR light mode
5. Future AI edits will compound the damage

**When in doubt, use the most restrictive option (Theme token).**

---

## Simplicity Principle

Prefer mental simplicity over architectural cleverness.

If you find yourself needing:
- multiple imports from design-system
- complex viz configuration
- custom renderers or scales

→ You are over-engineering. Use `useDesignViz()` and move on.
